DESCRIPTION: Above this number the sotmotion driver send a warning. Its time, no new data is received from encoder an internal counter increases its value by 1000, decresing by 1 each no problem iteration

NAME: Softmotion Number of Electric Turns
DESCRIPTION: Number of electrica turns in for the axis. This is the number of poles

NAME: Softmotion Speed From Position
DESCRIPTION: If true the speed is calculated from position data, otherwise the EIB speed will be used

NAME: Softmotion Tracking margin acceleration
DESCRIPTION: This acceleration is the margin available acceleration when axis is in tracking mode. This is used by tracking algorithm from the maximun available for tracking/slewing when slewing.

NAME: Softmotion Tracking margin jerk
DESCRIPTION: This acceleration is the margin available jerk when axis is in tracking mode. This is used by tracking algorithm from the maximun available for tracking/slewing when slewing.

NAME: Softmotion Tracking margin speed
DESCRIPTION: This acceleration is the margin available jerk when axis is in tracking mode. This is used by tracking algorithm from the maximun available for tracking/slewing when slewing.

NAME: Softmotion Tracking max acceleration
DESCRIPTION: This acceleration is the maximun available acceleration when axis is in tracking mode. This is used for tracking and slewing combination

NAME: Softmotion Tracking max jerk
DESCRIPTION: This jerk is the maximun available acceleration when axis is in tracking mode. This is used for tracking and slewing combination

NAME: Softmotion Tracking max speed
DESCRIPTION: This jerk is the maximun available speed when axis is in tracking mode. This is used for tracking and slewing combination

NAME: Stabilization Time
DESCRIPTION: Time to wait after finding references in Homming process

NAME: Subsystem Path
DESCRIPTION: Defines the subsystem path when an error must be transmitted

NAME: TCS Default Acceleration
DESCRIPTION: Default acceleration in TCS command mode

NAME: TCS Default Jerk
DESCRIPTION: Default Jerk in TCS command mode

NAME: TCS Default Velocity
DESCRIPTION: Default velocity in TCS command mode

NAME: TCS Max Acceleration
DESCRIPTION: Maximun allowed acceleration in TCS command mode

NAME: TCS Max Jerk
DESCRIPTION: Maximum Jerk in TCS command mode

NAME: TCS Max Velocity
DESCRIPTION: Maximun allowed velocity in TCS command mode

NAME: Timeout for Ack CW
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for receive and ack from Cable Wrap

NAME: Timeout for Ack EIB
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for receive and ack from EIB

NAME: Timeout for Axis Disable
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for disable axis and drives in the softmotion axis

NAME: Timeout for Axis Enable
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for enable axis and drives in the softmotion axis

NAME: Timeout for Brake Engage
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for engaging brakes

NAME: Timeout for Brake Release
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for releasing brakes

NAME: Timeout for Cable Wrap Power Off
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for power off cable wrap

NAME: Timeout for Cable Wrap Power On
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for power on cable wrap

NAME: Timeout for EnableTracking
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for enabling the tracking

NAME: Timeout for Fault Stop
DESCRIPTION: Timeout margin to stop when a fault is detected

NAME: Timeout for Homming
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for perform a homming operation

NAME: Timeout for Power Off
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for all power off sequence

NAME: Timeout for Power On
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for all power on sequence

NAME: Timeout for Reset
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for reseting actions

NAME: Timeout for Reset Axis
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for reseting axis faults

NAME: Timeout for Stop
DESCRIPTION: Margin for a standard stop

NAME: Timeout for Stop in Homing
DESCRIPTION: Timeout margin for stopping homing operation

NAME: Timeout Move Margin
DESCRIPTION: Margin for a movement

NAME: Traking Consecutive tracking command timeout
DESCRIPTION: After the firs tracking command is received, the time to generate and error if another tracking command is not received

NAME: Traking First tracking command timeout
DESCRIPTION: After the enable tracking command is received, the time to generate and error if a tracking command is not received

NAME: Traking Time offset
DESCRIPTION: Time offset to apply to received command time in tracking command

NAME: Horn Time (s)
DESCRIPTION: Time that the horn will be sounding

NAME: Light Time (s)
DESCRIPTION: Time that the light will be lighting

NAME: Commands to update settings
DESCRIPTION: When the number of commands to track ambient temperature set in this settings is received by the task, the settings will be updated

NAME: Critical High Cabinet Temperature
DESCRIPTION: This is the temperature at which an alarm is triggered.

NAME: Critical Low Cabinet Temperature
DESCRIPTION: This is the temperature at which an alarm is triggered.

NAME: DefaultSetpoint
DESCRIPTION: The setpoint sent when initializing, exiting and when going to fault in the Cabinet OMT.

NAME: High Cabinet Temperature
DESCRIPTION: Temperature causing a warning.

NAME: High Surface Temperature
DESCRIPTION: The difference between ambient temperature and surface temperature is above the allowed one

NAME: IP address
DESCRIPTION: This is the IP address of the RMC for the modbus connection.

NAME: Low Cabinet Temperature
DESCRIPTION: Temperature causing a warning.

NAME: Low Surface Temperature
DESCRIPTION: The difference between ambient temperature and surface temperature is bellow the allowed one

NAME: Lower Limit Hysteresis Relative
DESCRIPTION: This is the lower temperature limit  relative to the ambient temperature for the hysteresis control used when RMC is not working

NAME: Maximum Setpoint Temperature
DESCRIPTION: Maximum allowed temperature for setpoint

NAME: Minimum Setpoint Temperature
DESCRIPTION: Minimum allowed temperature for setpoint

NAME: port
DESCRIPTION: This is the connection port for the modbus of the RMC.

NAME: Special Error Lower Limit
DESCRIPTION: The error numbers between this setting and the Special Error Upper Limit will trigger the special fault in the main cabinet statechart. This special fault will trigger a fault in all subsystem to prepare for a possible cabinet switch off.

NAME: Special Error Upper Limit
DESCRIPTION: The error numbers between this setting and the Special Error Lower Limit will trigger the special fault in the main cabinet statechart. This special fault will trigger a fault in all subsystem to prepare for a possible cabinet switch off.

NAME: SystemSource
DESCRIPTION: This is the identifier for the system used when publishing the Alarm source.

NAME: Upper Limit Hysteresis Relative
DESCRIPTION: This is the upper temperature limit  relative to the ambient temperature for the hysteresis control used when RMC is not working

NAME: SystemSource
DESCRIPTION: This is the identifier for the system used when publishing the Alarm source.

NAME: CW Power Off
DESCRIPTION: Control Word value for powering off the MPS

NAME: CW Power On
DESCRIPTION: Control Word value for powering on the MPS

NAME: CW Reset
DESCRIPTION: Control Word value for resetting the error of the MPS

NAME: MaxCurrent
DESCRIPTION: This is the maximum allowed curent, above this value an alarm is sent.

NAME: MaxCurrentWarning
DESCRIPTION: This is the maximum allowed curent, above this value a warning is sent.

NAME: MaxPowerOnVoltage
DESCRIPTION: This is the maximum allowed voltage for enabling power on, if the voltage is above this value the power on command in idle is rejected.

NAME: MinVoltage
DESCRIPTION: This is the minimum allowed voltage, bellow this value an alarm is sent.

NAME: MinVoltageWarning
DESCRIPTION: This is the minimum allowed voltage, bellow this value a warning is sent.

NAME: Powering time out
DESCRIPTION: Timeout of the powering process

NAME: Reseting time
DESCRIPTION: Waiting time between the MPS reset and clearing faults

NAME: Wait Power Off In Fault
DESCRIPTION: Time to wait before sending switch off to Power supply

NAME: MinElevationPosition
DESCRIPTION: Minimum Elevation Position for the mirror cover to close.

DESCRIPTION: This is the identifier for the system used when publishing the Alarm source.

NAME: WaitTrans_Timeout
DESCRIPTION: Wait transition timeout

DESCRIPTION: The deployed position.

DESCRIPTION: WARNING! This setting is used to disable the colision check (value TRUE), use only when something is wrong. Otherwise leave it to FALSE.

DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the tank to cool down during the observation sequence

DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the transition between automatic and manual mode, in secods.

NAME: powerOffCoolingTimeout
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the cooling system to power off

NAME: powerOffMainPumpTimeout
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the main pump system to power off

NAME: powerOffOilCirculationTimeout
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the oil circulation system to power off

NAME: powerOnCoolingTimeout
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the cooling system to power on

NAME: powerOnMainPumpTimeout
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the main pump system to power on

NAME: powerOnOilCirculationTimeout
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the oil circulation system to power on

NAME: ResettingTime
DESCRIPTION: Timeout for the reset transition.

NAME: SystemSource
DESCRIPTION: This is the identifier for the system used when publishing the Alarm source.

NAME: watchdogMaximumTime
DESCRIPTION: Maximum time that the controller will wait without a watchdog signal

NAME: Fault Iterations Safety NoOk
DESCRIPTION: This is a counter used to trigger the Safety NO OK variable as TRUE if the value is greater than the set value.

NAME: Monitoring Timeout ms
DESCRIPTION: This is the timeout for the monitoring task in the TMA safety code.

NAME: OverrideCausesTimeout
DESCRIPTION: This is the timeout for executing the override causes command.

NAME: ResetCausesNumberOfChecks
DESCRIPTION: This is a setting used to trigger a warning that tells that some causes persist and were not restored. The trigger is sent if the number of checks is greater or equal to this setting value.

NAME: ResetCausesTimeBeforeChecking s
DESCRIPTION: Time to wait before checking that the causes were reseted.

NAME: ResetCausesTimeBetweenChecking s
DESCRIPTION: Time to wait between checking that the causes were reseted.

NAME: ResetCausesTimeout
DESCRIPTION: This is the timeout for executing the reset causes command.

NAME: RT to Safety Clock ms
DESCRIPTION: This is the RT to safety clock time value.

NAME: Safety Clock ms
DESCRIPTION: This is the safety clock time value.

NAME: AfterCommanderLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait after launching the commander

NAME: BeforeAmbientTemperatureTaskLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the Ambient Temperature task

NAME: BeforeAZMotorThermalLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the azimuth motor thermal control task

NAME: BeforeBALLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the balancing task

NAME: BeforeBoschLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the bosch task

NAME: BeforeBoschPowerSupplyLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the bosch power supply task

NAME: BeforeCabinet0101LaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the cabinet 0101 thermal control task

NAME: BeforeCabinetLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the cabinet task

NAME: BeforeCCWLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the azimuth motor thermal control task

NAME: BeforeDPLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the deployable platform task

NAME: BeforeELMotorThermalLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the azimuth motor thermal control task

NAME: BeforeIOTelemetryPublicationLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the IO Telemetry publication task

NAME: BeforeLPLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the locking pins task

NAME: BeforeMainAxesOMTTaskLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the OMT tasks for Main Axes

NAME: BeforeMainAxesPXICommTaskLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the task to communicate with the Axes PXI

NAME: BeforeMainAxisLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the main axis task

NAME: BeforeMCLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the mirror cover task

NAME: BeforeMCLLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the mirror cover lock task

NAME: BeforeModbusTempControllersLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the Modbus temperature controllers task

NAME: BeforeMPSLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the main power supply task

NAME: BeforeOSSLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the deployable platform task

NAME: BeforeSafetyLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the safety task

NAME: BeforeTECLaunchWait
DESCRIPTION: This is the time to wait before launching the TEC task

NAME: LocalRemote timeout
DESCRIPTION: After this time the Top End chiller checking for local remote change will send a timeout error

NAME: Power ON/OFF timeout
DESCRIPTION: After this time the Top End chiller checking for power on or off will send a timeout error

NAME: Reset pulse time
DESCRIPTION: Time of the reset pulse sent to Top en chiller controller

NAME: AverageSampleLength
DESCRIPTION: This is the sample number used to make the error average to compare it with the MaxAllowedError and finish the slewing movement. This value is used for both the Azimuth and Elevation axes.

NAME: Azimuth Slew Threshold
DESCRIPTION: Minimum position change that would consider a tracking command as slewing for azimuth axis

NAME: Command queue size
DESCRIPTION: Size of the queue which receives the LSST commands

NAME: Elevation Slew Threshold
DESCRIPTION: Minimum position change that would consider a tracking command as slewing for elevation axis

NAME: Final motion behaviour
DESCRIPTION: Define how the algorithm works after reaching desired point. 0 for keep velocity and 1 for recalculation

NAME: MaxAllowedError
DESCRIPTION: This is the maximum allowed error for the trajectory generation. Is used to stop the slewing movement and start the tracking. This value is used for both azimuth and elevation axes.

NAME: Number of Axes
DESCRIPTION: Number of reflexxes axes. DO NOT FORGET SYNCHRONIZATION AXIS. For example for azimuth and elevation axis you need 3 axis.

NAME: Reflexxess dll path
DESCRIPTION: Path in the PXI where the reflexxess dll is stored

NAME: Synchronization behaviour
DESCRIPTION: Manage the synchronization of axis when generating trajectory. 3 no synchroniation and 1 time synchronization

NAME: Time Setpoint offset
DESCRIPTION: Time to add to setpoint time to adjust the delays. It should at least be one scan engine execution time.

NAME: Wait for data before error
DESCRIPTION: The trajectory generator waits this time for data before sending an error

NAME: Waiting time for setpoint time
DESCRIPTION: Time to sleep the setpoint receiving task before checking again if the setpoint time is the actual time.

NAME: Waiting time if no data
DESCRIPTION: Time to sleep the setpoint receiving task before checking if new data is available.
